sub_title: XRF student lab assistant & MSc student Geology & Geochemistry at Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam
summary:
I am a first year MSc student in Geology & Geochemistry at the VU Amsterdam. Alongside my studies, I work as a student assistant in the XRF geochemical lab. My goal is to solidify my career in academia by pursuing a PhD. 
My current MSc research project is about Iceland's newest volcano: Fagradalsfjall. In this project, which is a continuation of my BSc thesis, I combine geochemical (isotope) data of whole rock samples and olivine-hosted melt inclusions to better understand the heterogeneous Icelandic mantle.
